reviewText: 1. Six-Man Tag Team Match: The Dudley Boys vs. Rey Mysterio, Paul London, and Billy KidmanGood way to open the show, and a decent tag match. 5.5/102. Till Death Do us Part Match- Lita Marries the Winner: Matt Hardy vs. KaneEven though this is a bit short, I liked this match. It had some good back and forth action, and a couple nice spots. The ending is good too. Worth a watch, even if it is short. 6/103. Match #1 in a Best of 5 Series for the United States Championship: Booker T (c) vs. John CenaFar too short, only about 5 or so minutes. Decent I suppose, but way to short to even review. Only 5 minutes for a title match? Worth seeing once, but there really isn't much here. 5/104. Triple Threat Match for the Intercontinental Championship: Edge vs. Batista vs. Chris JerichoA good match, but Batista seemed a little out of place and a tad sloppy. Crowd is solidly behind Jericho, which the commentators continued to point out as "odd". I didn't find it suprising, because Edge was a very stale face, and Jericho is clearly the best wrestler of the three. Pretty good, but yet another match that falls too short, this one is only about 10 minutes. 6.5/105. Eddie Guerrero vs. Kurt AngleA good match, but even this one is a bit short. These two deserve more then a lame 13 minutes. They do the best with the time they have tho, and even if this is a little slow, its still a good match. Not better then their match from Wrestlemania XX, but still good. Definitely worth watching. 7.5/106. Triple H vs. EugeneWhy is the WWE so fascinated with shoving Eugene down our throats? He is positively awful in the ring, and has an even worse gimmick. The great Toronto crowd really lets him have it in this one, which is a much welcome breath of fresh air. Not very bad, but not very good either. Worth seeing once I suppose, if only to see that piece of trash Eugene get beaten pretty badly by The Game. Better then expected, but thats not saying too much. 5.5/107. Diva Dodgeball: Don't even bother. Even the eye candy doesn't make it worth watching. Skip this, please. 0/108. WWE Championship Match: JBL (c) vs. The UndertakerI had heard many reviews that stated that this was an awful car wreck of a match that wasn't even worth watching, so I was naturally curious as to how bad this was. Quite frankly, this isn't the piece of trailer trash that many would have you believe, but it isn't anything to write home about either. This is surprising for the Undertaker, but it is to be expected from JBL. This match is tolerable, but not worth watching more then once. 5/109. World Heavyweight Championship Match: Chris Benoit (c) vs. Randy OrtonI really enjoyed this matchup. Very back and forth, these two really do their best to make this one exciting. They also give this one the perfect amount of time, the ending clocks in at about the 20 minute mark. I didn't really like Benoit as champion, but he certainly gave us good title defenses. This match is no exception. Randy Orton proves in this match why he deserves to be in main events such as this. He is a great heel character, and a good wrestler on top of that. Very good title bout between these two, with a great pace. I like the ending too, the right man wins this one. 8.75/10This Summerslam suprised me. With so many reviews saying to avoid this one at all costs, I was expecting this to be nothing but a mess. Overall, this is a decent Summerslam, though the undercard is seriously lacking, not in match quality, but in match length. The uppercard picks up, and the two title matches were quite good. JBL and 'Taker is an underrated match, don't listen to others who pan this one. The night ends on a good note too.Match of the Night: Benoit vs. Orton. Great title match, these two give it their all and put on a very good match.

reviewText: <50: Ask for a refund for not only your money, but also your time. [F] (G.A.Bash '04)50-54: Mediocre & disappointing. [D] (EG: Judgment Day '04)55-59: Average. [C] (EG: Royal Rumble '04 & No Way Out '04)60-64: Worth A Watch. [C+] (EG: Vengeance '04)65-69: Good event that was worth the money. [B] (EG: WrsetleMania 20)70-74: Very good. [B+] (EG: WrestleMania 19)75-79: Make sure you add this ppv to your video or dvd collection. [A] (EG: SummerSlam '02)80+ : Make sure that the video or dvd is locked in a safe & cannot be erased. Memorable. [A+]BUH-BUH RAY, D-VON & SPIKE DUDLEY defeated REY MYSTERIO, BILLY KIDMAN & PAUL LONDON: Well-paced opener which is how the WWE should open up any pay-per-view involving the SmackDown roster. Although, the live crowd did take quite a while to get into the match (if anything, it was London's aerial skills that woke them up). Both the faces & the heels did their jobs well & there were enough spots to keep everyone entertained. The bout probably needed another 4 or 5 minutes, as at 8 minutes in length, it just couldn't build up as effectively to the entertaining climax. Nowhere near perfect, but a handy little opener. Match Rating...7KANE defeated MATT HARDY in a 'Til Death Do Us Part' Match: The pace from the opener didn't let up here, as Matt brought his A-game to Toronto. More intense than their 'N0-DQ' match from Vengeance, the short length (7 minutes) of this bout actually worked in it's favor. Good psychology as Matt never let up on the pace & logically even went for a countout win. Well booked ending with Matt knowing that he was only one big move away from victory & going to the top rope for that move. But the only thing he received was an awesome top-rope chokeslam. Surprisingly good match in an ordinary storyline. Well done to both men. Match Rating...7JOHN CENA defeated BOOKER T in the 1st Match of a Best of 5 Series for the United States Title: Disappointing match which not only took a while to get going, but started off very sloppily. Cena & Booker almost appeared as if they had never been in the ring together!!! They eventually started to mesh though & as the pace started to quicken, the crowd got involved in what was becoming a very good bout. Then it just ended..... at the 7 minute mark!!! Way too much of an anti-climax for an important match such as this. The structure of this bout very much let it down & these 2 can do so much better. Match Rating...6EDGE defeated CHRIS JERICHO & BATISTA in a Triple-Threat Match to Retain the InterContinental Title: Good dynamics in this match, as there was enough variation between the 3 competitors. Batista's power & the crowd favoritism of Jericho over Edge really helped to make this bout quite good. As per usual in Triple-Threat matches, the 3 combatants were hardly all in the ring at the same time, but that's almost expected nowadays. The main problem with this bout though, was that it was a little too fast-paced!!! Or to be more correct, a little too helter-skelter. This resulted in too many moves being performed for basically no reason at all, and a general lack of psychology in the match. Still pretty good though. Match Rating...7KURT ANGLE defeated EDDIE GUERRERO: Very good match which was basically a shortened version of their WrestleMania 20 bout. I think the fact that both men were not quite at their fittest held this 14 minute match back a little, but not all that much. Almost UFC style in structure (& to some extent, pacing), both men almost immediately went for each other's ankle & so began an excellent battle of cat & mouse. Angle looked superb in his major return bout, while Eddie was impressive in matching & countering Kurt's technical skills. It was logical & sensible that the constant ankle work would not lead to the fastest paced climax, and while they still turned it up a notch, that probably stopped this bout from getting a higher ranking. I'm also not sure if it was a good move to have Angle kick out of Eddie's Frog Splash!!! I wouldn't say "no" to a return match at 'No Mercy', as this was my match of the night!!! Match Rating...8TRIPLE H defeated EUGENE: I will go into it in greater detail later in my 'Dessert' topic, but just a note that the following review was done with the sound turned down!!! I really liked this 14 minute match. Triple H played the heel role perfectly (not that you would know with the sound on), while Eugene really stepped it up a notch inside the squared circle. While Dinsmore's style is unorthodox, his enthusiasm more than made up for it during this bout. Greater intensity here mixed really well against Triple H. Very entertaining with Triple H continuing to play the sadistic, humorous & brutal villain, all in one. While Eugene's Rock Bottom, Stone Cold Stunner & Big Boot/Legdrop combo all fitted perfectly into different parts of the match. To cap it all off, we saw a well booked finish involving Flair & Regal. Plus, the correct wrestler won the match relatively cleanly. I can see this match being under-rated & it really does deserve multiple viewings!!! Match Rating...8TEAM DREAM defeated TEAM DIVA in a Divas Dodgeball Match: Firstly, I found it hilarious that Carmella Charisma didn't grace us with her pleasure for this game!!! The WWE must turn that into a mini-angle to make this Diva Search mildly amusing. While this had no value being included on this card, it luckily only wasted 5 minutes. Nothing was really learnt & I suppose the WWE did a good job of making an issue of whether or not Gail Kim should have been thrown out of the game. An effective little toilet break, but there is no way I can pass it. Match Rating...4JOHN BRADSHAW LAYFIELD defeated THE UNDERTAKER by Disqualification to Retain the WWE Championship: I'm getting ready for a bagging on this one..... Nowhere near as bad as it could have been. In fact, it was quite a good big man match, with enough variation to make it more than satisfactory. At 18 minutes (plus a 4 minute aftermath, which included JBL being chokeslammed through his limo), the bout definitely lasted a few minutes too long. 12-15 minutes would have been about right. The DQ ending was also a definite disappointment, although it sort of makes sense from a short to medium-term booking perspective. Plus, that's why the aftermath existed. Well booked (apart from the length), I liked the good (& clever) leg work done by JBL early on. There were also a couple of good spots (EG: the simultaneous big boots). Both men gave a pretty good performance & I think saved what was a pretty ordinarily set up feud. Match Rating...7RANDY ORTON defeated CHRIS BENOIT to Win the World HeavyWeight Title: Much like the pay-per-view as a whole, this was a very solid, if unspectacular, main event. It definitely lacked something that a big main event match should have, but I can't really put my finger on it. Maybe it was a general lack of excitement, pace and/or spots. Apart from that though, it's hard to fault the bout too much. The result aside, which I feel is too soon, Orton continued to show signs of great potential & improvement. But he also showed the same usual signs of inexperience. Benoit was his usual intense self & his exceptional selling went to another level here. The fantastically booked ending came at the 20 minute mark when Orton literally hit the RKO out of nowhere. That ending alone almost legitimized the move right up there with DDP's 'Diamond Cutter' & Steve Austin's 'Stone Cold Stunner'. Solid match. NOTE: This match almost made me rethink my policy of not giving half marks on my ratings. It was probably a 7 & 1/2, but I will be a little harsh on it as it was the main event of a big ppv..... Match Rating...7PPV RATING (61/90) = 68Looking at the key, I have basically given 'SummerSlam' a 'B' grade & said it was a 'good event that was worth the money'. I don't have any problem with that rating. I don't think many people will rate the ppv as high as I have, but I question how much of that is due to their personal dislike of feuds/matches/wrestlers. Not to mention the live crowd which I will get to in a minute. There is no doubt that nothing stood out at the event, and this is what weighed the card down. It won't be a memorable ppv as such, but it was an extremely solid one. I really think that an extra 15 minutes added to this ppv (split evenly between 3 of the first 4 matches) would have topped this off perfectly. Definitely a card where each individual will have to judge for themselves, but just like some movies, I think this might get better with repeated viewings.

reviewText: After several dissapointing WWE PPVS, Summerslam proved that the WWE is still capable of listening to it's fans and can provide them with quality matches and suprises.The Six-Man Tag Team Match was a generally amazing effort, the Dudley Boyz pick up the win.Matt Hardy vs Kane: Given that Hardy had an injury entering the match, don't expect a lengthy encounter here, instead expect Matt fighting his injury to pull off a short fine match with Kane, watch out Kane's finishing choke-slam from the top ropeTriple Threat Match for the Intercontinental Championship: Edge vs Chris Jericho vs Batista: The crowd boo Edge out of the building as he defens the intercontinental Championship against Jericho and Batista, pretty good given Jericho and Edge deliver the better moments of the match, Edge eventually panders to the crowd and acts more like a heel before sprearing Jericho after he is distratced by Batista to retain the title.Kurt Angle vs Eddie Guerrero: A superb match, even better than thier last effort at Wrestlemania 20, Angle and Guerrero tell a story by re-telling what happened at Wrestlemania 20...only this time Angle is ready for anything Guerrero tries, "Latino Heat" falls to the Ankle LockTriple H vs Eugene: God bless Canada, as they finally bring down Eugene by booing him out of the building, realtivly good match considering Eugene;s move set has become somehow limited, Hunter carries the load, but his no-selling is completly ridculous (he kicks out of FOUR FINISHERS from Eugene) he finally defeats Eugene with a pedigree after Ric Flair and William Regal interfere on behalf of Hunter and Eugene respectivly.WWE Championship: The Undertaker vs J.B.L: The Toronto crowd again could'nt care for this match, they eventually began performing a FREAKING MEXICAN WAVE because they were so horrendously "bored", the match itself is fine, and better than mot Undertaker matches, J.B.L used some old school submission manuvers and made use of his "Cheif of Security" Orlando Jordan, he also kicks out of several finishers from the 'TakerThe ending is not pretty, and niether is the bump J.B..L takes when 'Taker choke-slams him through his limo.World Heavyweight Championship: Randy Orton vs Chris Benoit: The fienst wrestler next to Bret Hart carries Randy Orton to a clasic encounter, the crowd was too busy insulting Earl Hebner to even care though, Orton destroys Benoit by preventing the crossface from locking in and hits an R.K.O to become champion, therby putting the buy rates of the company on his shoulders.An excellent PPV, and proof the WWE is far from finished when it coems to excellent booking.

reviewText: Rey Mysterio, Paul London, Billy Kidman vs. Dudley Boyz & Spike Dudley - London & Kidman upset the Dudleys to win the tag team titles while Spike turned heel, won the Crusierweight title, and was "The Boss" of the Dudleys.  This was a good 6 man tag opener that didn't get dull.Kane vs. Matt Hardy - This was from the Kane/Lita/Hardy storyline in which Lita was having Kane's baby (long story that I'm sure nobody wants to remember) & the winner of this match would get to marry Lita. Hardy bumped like crazy & tried everything to stop Kane but he was just overpowered in the end.(Also available on Kane's DVD)United States Champion Booker T vs. John Cena - This was match 1 of their best of 5 series. This was a solid encounter as Booker T was one of the guys who can bring out the best in John Cena. One of the best matches from their series.Intercontinental Championship Edge vs. Batista vs. Chris Jericho - This was one of the signs that this was an "unusual" crowd as Edge was a babyface yet booed in his hometown.  Edge & Jericho put on a great performance like they usually do with Batista being able to keep up with his powerful offense.Eddie Guerrero vs. Kurt Angle - This was sightly a stepdown from their WrestleMania match but that doesn't mean they didn't put on one of the best performances of the night.  You know that whenever you get these two together, you have a classic encounter on your hands & this was no exception.Triple H vs. Eugene - Eugene's overpush was over as the crowd completely turned against Eugene & this wasn't a great match for Triple H to have.  It was decent at best which is a damn shame concidering how Triple H is one of the best in the business today & Nick Densmore is good in the ring when he's not handicapped by the Eugene gimmick.Diva Dodgeball - Pointless divas segment.  Unless you like looking at them in fitness outfits, skip.WWE Champion J.B.L. vs. Undertaker - The crowd turned on this match too (I think they were doing the wave at one point) as it was just really slow & they were off at times. It's watchable but their No Mercy match heavily made up for this.World Heavyweight Champion Chris Benoit vs. Randy Orton - This match was the peak of Randy Orton's career as he lived up to his true potential in this match & put on a wrestling clinic with Chris Benoit.  Depending on which shipment of DVD's you have, the audio goes out in the last 10-15 mins.  Again, a great match in the career of Orton who goes on to become the youngest champion in history (sorry Brock!)DVD extras include all of the "Summer Olympic" paraodies including one where Batista is breakdancing (you read that one right) along with behind the scenes footage, a Heat match between RVD & Rene Dupree, and two backstage segments with Benoit & Guerrero, and Evolution.Overall, this was a good SummerSlam from top to bottom & one of the top evenets from 2004 that I recommend.

reviewText: I say that obviously because of one match but I'll get to that later. Here is the card:The Dudley Boyz (Team 3-D) Vs. Rey Mysterio, Paul London & Billy Kidman - Surprisingly good opener! Lots of cool spots and fast action!Matt Hardy Vs. Kane - The winner of this match got to "marry" Lita. With Matt leaving at the time to get knee surgery and the fact he beat Kane at the previous PPV (Vengeance 2004), it was pretty obvious that Kane was going to win this one as he dominated the majority of this match. Still, not a bad bout.Booker T. Vs. John Cena - This was match 1 in a best of 5 series between the two for Booker's United States Championship! While John Cena has never been the greatest ring performer, I thought he showed more during this period than he does now. During this period, he was basically "Stone Cold" Steve Austin but without the beer, much of the cussing and was from a hip-hop angle than hard rock.Anyway, Booker and Cena did do good work for the short time that they had together in the ring for this event! Booker, as usual, carried this bout but Cena kept up with him very well.Edge Vs. Chris Jericho Vs. Batista - This was a Triple Threat match for Edge's I-C title and one of Batista's first shots as a singles champion. Surprisingly, the fans were cheering for Chris Jericho even though they were wrestling in Edge's hometown of Toronto, Canada!As for the match itself, Batista was really built up prior to this as he had "knocked" out both Jericho and Edge on seperate occassions prior to this bout with a clothesline so it was a surprise when Edge retained the title with a pinfall win over Jericho. Wasn't the best Triple Threat but not bad.Eddie Guerrero Vs. Kurt Angle - A rematch of their WrestleMania XX bout where Eddie retained the WWE title against Angle. This time, Angle had Luther Reigns at ringside but he had very little to do with the outcome as Angle pretty much outwrestled Guerrero after several minutes of back and forth action between the two and got his revenge with a tapout victory against Eddie.Diva Dodgeball - Other than seeing beautiful women in tight outfits, this is worth one view. I'd skip it though you do see some familiar faces here.Triple H Vs. Eugene - Pretty much a squash though Eugene had his moments. This is one of the few times I was 100% behind HHH and was glad to see him win over Eugene! Even the fans in Canada, who normally would boo "The Game", cheered him as if he was the good guy!The Undertaker Vs. JBL - This was for the WWE title and, to be honest, it was an okay bout at best. The crowd thought so too as they weren't into this match at all!Chris Benoit Vs. Randy Orton - This was for the World Heavyweight Title and was one of Randy's best matches! Despite what he did in June 2007 to his family, I will still give Chris Benoit credit for making Randy look the best he had looked up until that point. Randy deserves credit as well as he wrestled probably the best mat style bout he ever had at that point.Orton, of course, won the title and the aftermatch is both touching and very sad especially when you think of the events from last June. I can't help sometimes but wonder what does Randy Orton think now?There are a few extras but one was a quiet talk between Eddie Guerrero and Chris Benoit, both of whom are now deceased. Its touching, haunting and even uncomfortable to watch knowing what we know now on both stars (especially Benoit). Still, as I have said on many occassions, I will not forget the history even if WWE chooses too. To do so would dishonor the careers of all the men that Chris wrestled and to do so would mean forgetting his wife and son that he murdered (something that I will NEVER do).Back to the DVD card itself, it is a mixed bag of matches. Some good, one was great and a few others forgettable. At best, this is a 4-star card but no worse than a 3. I choose to give it 4. My understanding is that this full card WILL be on the upcoming SummerSlam anthology (including the Benoit/Orton bout). Anyway, a decent card with one historic bout.
summary: A Great Card But An Ominous Look Back

reviewText: The best ppv since Wrestlemania. Excellent extras such as all the hilirous commercials for Summerslam. WWE experienced audio problems halfway through. there was no sound for the rest of the match. aftermath is a must see!a must see after the PPV between Chris Benoit & Eddie Guerrero.WWE needs to cut back to 4 ppvs a year. get rid of the one brand ppvs & have them come together 4 times a year. the quality of wrestling & entertainment would be much better.

reviewText: All I can say is wow! When the final card was decided and the stage was set for Summerslam, I didn't think this event could deliver, but boy was I wrong. I can honestly say that no match was bad and the main-event caliber matches really pushed the envelope for mutually great performances by both competitors. Eddie and the returning to in-ring-action Angle put on yet another mat masterpiece that may even surpass their Wrestlemania XX outing.  Also, Undertaker vs. JBL shocked me in the fact that they didn't wrestle the archetypal big man vs. big man match. The move for move pacing was much quicker than expected and Undertaker shook up his usual "Deadman" move arsenal by showcasing a new repoitore of submission maneuvers. And finally, the unexpected yet pleasant surprise of Orton winning the title really put this event over the top in his and Benoit's classic encounter. In short, WWE really raised the bar with this installment of Summerslam by showcasing the talented roster WWE posses by putting on one helluva pay-per-view.

reviewText: Very good PPV.  It is probably the best PPV of the year as far as match quality goes.  Almost all of the matches were very good, compared to most PPV's were there is only 2-3 really good matches.1. Spike & Dudley Boys vs. Bill Kidman, Paul London, Rey Mysterio (6 Man Tag)Great way to kick off the show.  Very fast paced, exciting match.  London is really an upcoming star.  Good match.  (8.5/10)2. Kane vs. Matt Hardy (Til' Death Do Us Part Match)Short match, but still pretty good.  Good ring bell shot by Matt on Kane.  Great top rope Chokeslam by Kane.  Another good match.  (8/10)3. John Cena vs. Booker (Match #1 in the Best of 5 Series to Determine the U.S. Champ)Very short match and not that entertaining.  The 3 other matches so far have been much better.  They did this to get the two on the card.  (7/10)4. Edge vs. Chris Jericho vs. Batista (Intercontinental Title/Triple Threat)Pretty entertaing match.  It is relatively slow for a triple threat match, but it was still good.  The slower pace was new for a triple threat match, but made for a good match.  It was sloppy at times, but I think that was expected.  Good match, nonetheless.  (8/10)5. Eddie Guerrro vs. Kurt AngleBest match of the night and one of the top 5 of the year so far, in my opinion.  Finally, Angle is off the disabled list and wrestling well.  Good chemistry in the match.  Great technical match with a very good ending.  (9/10)6. Triple H vs. EugeneTriple H destroys Eugene for most of the match, but it was made out to be pretty entertaing.  Good emotion in the match.  Decent ending.  (8/10)7. Undertaker vs. JBL (WWE Championship)Very, very boring match.  The crowd was really booing throughout most of the match.  Horrible ending.  Good post match action as Taker Chokeslams JBL through the top of the limo. Watch for Taker slipping on the limo.  (They may have edited this out).  Pretty funny.  Worst match of the night.  (6/10)8. Chris Benoit vs. Randy Orton (World Heavyweight Title)Great match.  Another top ten of the year candidate.  Great spot when Benoit goes for the suicide dive and misses and hits the barricade.  I really though he hurt his neck when this happened.  Very exciting last few minutes to the match.  Surprisng and abrupt ending.I would recommend picking up this PPV, b/c most of the matches are at least halway decent.Overall Rating:  8.5/10

reviewText: I watched Summerslam on ppv this morning and it was a pretty goood ppv but some matches were too short. Her is the card and how I rate the matches.*-Awful**-okay***-Average****-Good*****-ClassicDudley Boyz and Spike Dudley vs. Kidman/Londan and Mysterio-Good opener but I expected better from this match. It should have been 15 minutes long like the tag match at JD. Dudley Boyz win after hitting Londan with the belt and getting the pinfall.WINNERS-DUDLEY BOYZ/SPIKE ***Kane vs. Matt Hardy-Til Death do us part Match-Very short match with not much action and only a few wrestling moves used. Kane picks up the victory after a top rope choke slam and is going to marrie Lita. Lita's heel turn should have been in this match.WINNER-KANE **U.S Title Match 1-Booker T vs. John Cena-Another short match which should have been better. Cena wins after an F.U to Booker.WINNER-JOHN CENA ***Intercontinental Title-Edge vs. Jericho vs. Batista-Wow this was actually a great match with fast paced action and some good spots. Batista worked well in this match as did Jericho but Edge retained after Batista got thrown outside by Jericho and Edge hit the spear on Jericho for the three count.WINNER-EDGE ****Eddie Guerrero vs. Kurt Angle-Good match but not as good as their match at Wrestlemania 20. Kurt Angle looks great in the ring and Eddie dis well with his injury. Kurt wins his return match making Eddie tap out with the ankle lock. I cant beleive it the crowd was cheering for Kurt Angle woooooooooooo.WINNER-KURT ANGLE ****Triple H vs. Eugene-Decent match up between these two. I thought Eugene would win but Triple H won with the pedigree after Eugene was cheering for Regal coming to ringside. Eugene is a great talent and needs a better gimmick.WINNER-TRIPLE H ****JBL vs. The Undertaker-This match was a brawl all the way through. Still a great contest between two big men and Was approximatly 20 minutes long. Orlando Jordan interferes and gives Taker the Belt but JBl only gets a two count from a slow referee. Underaker hits the last ride but only gets a 2 count. Undertaker hits JBL with the championship belt but the ref sees and JBL retains by disqualification. Taker beats up JBL after the match.WINNER-JBL ****Chris Benoit vs. Randy Orton-Arn't Main Events usually the longest match of the night. Oh well this was still a great match. Benoit is the most entertaining technical wrestler ever and is a machine and Orton is a great upcoming talent. Both men did well in this match but why does Ortons opponent dominate him in every match. I would like to see Orton in controll for once to see what hes got. Orton wins the worlds title after Chris Benoit went for the Crossface but Orton countered into an R.K.O for a three count.WINNER-RANDY ORTON ****Overall a great Summerslam with a strong card and many great matches. Orton is the new champion and JBL was lucky to keep his belt. I advise you to buy this when it comes out on DVD.

reviewText: Summerslam 2004 was a very good ppv with plenty of good matches. Here is how I rate the matchesRATING SCALE40- Bad ppv40-50 okay ppv50-60Average ppv60-70-good ppv70-80 exellent ppv80+ classic ppvDudley Boyz def. Mysterio,London,Kidman TIME-8 minutesExellent underated match up. This match had high flying moves, fast paced action and a good angle behind it. Great way to kick off Summerslam 2004. WINNER-Dudley Boyz 8/10Kane def. Matt Hardy-Til Death Do Us Part Match TIME-6 minutesA good match for the time these two had to work with. Matt Hardy peformed well injured and suprisingly Kane put on one of his best matches this year. The ending was awsome and out of no where. WINNER-Kane 7/10U.S Championship-Best of 5 series match 1John Cena def. Booker T(c) TIME-7 minutesFirst real bad match of the night. These two are great wrestlers and should have done way better. WINNER-John Cena 4/10Intercontinental Championship-Triple Threat MatchEdge(c) def. Chris Jericho and Batista TIME-9 minutesOkay match but nothing special. Edge got booed out of his home town even though he won the match. All three wre never in the ring at the same time, it was always 1 on 1 which was a bit dissapointing. The finish came when Jericho knocked Batista to the outside with a springboard kick and got nailed by the spear when he turned around for the three count. WINNER-Edge 6/10Kurt Angle def. Eddie Guerrero TIME-13 minutesA very good contest but not as good as their match at WM 20. This match had alot of chain and technical wrestling at the start but got exciting at the end. Triple H dominated and it would have been better if Eugene did some of his moves because it would pump up the crowd. There was alot of brawling in this match but also alot of wrestling moves. In the end Flair comes out to distract Eugene but gets sent from ringside. Regal met Flair at the ramp and hit him with the brasp nuts but it distracted Eugene allowing Triple H to hit the pedigree and get the three count. Confusing finish!!!!!!!! WINNER-Triple H 7/10WWE ChampionshipJBL(c) def. The Undertaker TIME-18 minutesThis was a better match than people say it was but still wasn't great. I think takers chain wrestling bored the crowd. At one stage they did a mexican wave for about 3 minutes. Anyway a typical JBL match with loads of brawling and hardcore like action. JBL brings the chair in the ring but Taker kicks it back in his face and clocks him with it but the referee saw it and disqualifyed The Undertaker. After the match Undertaker beat JBL up by smashing him onto the front of the limo and chokeslammed him throught the limo. WINNER-JBL 6/10World Heavyweight ChampionshipRandy Orton def. reviewText: Despite the fact that Randy Orton won the world heavyweight title in the main event and became the youngest world champion of all time, This summerslam will be forgotten by me in a few years or so. This event doesn't even look that good on paper [Which is often a tell-tale sign of a bad pay-per-view]. But anyway, Here's my opinions on the matches that happened on this event:1. Rob Van Dam Vs. Rene DupreeThis match aired on heat shortly before the actual ppv broadcast began. This match is on this dvd as an extra feature. This match is nothing memorable, But it was a watchable match to say the least. I did love that long five star frog splash that RVD did in the end of this match. RVD wins. **1/22. Bubba Ray, D'Von, And Spike Dudley Vs. Billy Kidman, Rey Mysterio, And Paul LondonThis wasn't a very good way to start off the ppv. This match simply wasn't interesting despite the involvement of such talented wrestlers as The dudleys, Rey Mysterio, and Billy Kidman [I don't really care much for London]. This is just an average 6 man tag team match. I will say this, The storyline heading into this match was actually pretty good. Well, Over a year later, The dudleys are in TNA as Team 3D, Billy Kidman is no longer with the WWE, And Paul London has dissapeared. The Dudleys win. **3. Till death do us part match-Lita marries the winnerMatt Hardy Vs. KaneAnother mediocre match. This was also an uninteresting match. Only thing that was really cool about this match is the top rope chokeslam Kane delivered to Matt in the end. Ironically, At the very next Summerslam, Which happened just a few months ago, Matt would face Edge because of Lita [Who betrayed Kane for Edge earlier this year and interestingly enough left Matt for Edge in real life]. Kane won this match. **4. Match #1 of a best of 5 series for the WWE U.S. TitleChampion Booker T Vs. John CenaThis was just plain horrible. This whole series sucked and this match was definitely no exception. I hope this best of 7 series that they got Booker and Benoit in will turn out to be far better than this. Cena won, But i don't really think many people cared. *5. Triple Threat Intercontinental Title matchChampion Edge Vs. Chris Jericho Vs. BatistaThis was a better match than the 4 that proceeded it. This wasn't a good match, But it was decent. It's better than most of the other matches on here and for that, I will give this match credit. There was some good action throughout from these 3 guys.I'd say this match is worth a watch. It's still hard to believe that Batista would be world champion just 8 months after this match took place. Edge retained the I-C Title. ***6. Eddie Guerrero [RIP] Vs. Kurt AngleThis match truly saved this event from being worse than what it already was. Although not as good as their classic confrontation at wrestlemania 20, This match was action-packed and was pretty entertaining. Both guys done a great job in handling this match. This match was nice and it shows the kind of good match that much of the rest of this event is missing. Guerrero is sorely missed right now. He was like, One of the few things that kept smackdown interesting over the last 2 years before his death. Angle won this match. **** [Best match on the event]7. Eugene Vs. Triple HThis match wasn't all that bad. This match was actually pretty good at times. Last year, Eugene was becoming a very big attraction on raw when he made his debut. So big in fact, That he found his way into a feud with the game. I really enjoyed the story that lead up to this match. And while the match wasn't necessarily a classic, It's definitely worth the time it takes to watch it. Another interesting thing about this match was that Eugene performed several famous finishers on Triple H and despite all this, Triple H still was able to win this match, Due to interference from his then-evolution associate Ric Flair. This is another one of the matches that saved this event. ***1/28. Diva DodgeballSkip! No stars9. For the WWE World Heavyweight TitleChampion JBL Vs. The UndertakerThis match wasn't really good. By the time this match finally started to pick up some steam, The match wasn't far from being over. Undertaker was really manhandling JBL for a lot of this match. I personally would've been satisfied if Taker had defeated JBL here for the WWE title. But, The match ended with a disqualification and JBL was declared the winner meaning JBL was still champion. **10. For the World Heavyweight TitleChampion Chris Benoit Vs. Randy OrtonThis match wasn't really that much better than the smackdown title match that came before it, And if you ask me, This was a pretty lackluster main event. Both of these guys are good wrestlers, But admit it, Orton had no business being in this match on this event. While the match wasn't terrible, It's marred by the fact that an extremely talented wrestler like Benoit ended up dropping the title to a wrestler like Randy Orton. Benoit really deserved a far better ending to his title reign than this. Orton was a mediocre champion too. But, Things might not be as bad if Orton were to win the title now. Match was watchable, Even though it's ending dissapointed some. **1/2This summerslam wasn't good. I don't see why a lot of people liked this summerslam. Unless you're one of those who thinks that the WWE can never dissapoint you, You will most likely not find much to be joyful about when watching this summerslam. Hope the review helped. Be blessed.

reviewText: August 15, 2004 Air Canada Centre Toronto, CanadaThis is where it was made possible for youngster Randy Orton where he stepped out of Triple H's shadow and became the dominant member of Evolution. Triple H realized this the next night on Raw after Orton beat Chris Benoit for the second night in a row.Anyhoo, on to the PPV itself. The matches are out of 5 stars, they may not be in order, either.Rey Mysterio, Paul London, Billy Kidman vs. D-Von, Spike and Bubba Ray DudleyPretty good opener, I thought Rey, Paul and Billy worked good as a team. Tons of high-flying action (from one team, anyway) Kidman gets nailed with a 3-D and They allow Spike to get the pin. ***Booker T vs. John Cena (Match 1 of 5 for the U.S. Championship)Seemed kinda rushed, (It was as if everyone was working within a time-limit that night). Not a horrible match, watchable. Watch close for the ending as it comes out of nowhere. FU and Cena takes it. **Diva Dodgeball-Diva Search Contestants vs. WWE DivasWasste of time 1/2* (At Least you get to see 12 gorgeous women.)Edge vs. Batista vs. Chris Jericho-Triple Threat Match for the Intercontinental ChampionshipRealllly slow, not very good. No one wanted to continuously fight. They seemed to take a lot of breaks. I thought it was stupid for the canadians to boo their "hometown hero". Anyway, watchable. Edge wins with a spear on Jericho. *1/2.Kurt Angle vs. Eddie GuerreroGreat, Great match. These two produce another classic. 2nd best match of the night. I thought it was funny when Angle pulled off Eddie's boot and put the ankle lock on his socked foot. You could buy this for this match alone and not be upset at all. Ranks as one of my ten favorites of all time. As Does there Wrestlemania XX classic. Eddie taps to the Ankle Lock *****Til' Death Do Us Part Match-Kane vs. Matt HardyShort and sweet, lots of powerful moves on behalf of Kane, lots of fast-paced moves on behalf of Matt Hardy. This was a "styles-clash" match. Sick chokeslam from the top turnbuckle by Kane to put V1 down for the count.***Triple H vs. EugenePretty good match This match had a lengthy buildup, Triple H dominates for the majority of the match funny to see Eugene give Triple H his own move. Regal distracts Eugen accidentally so Triple H gives him a pedigree and covers him very fast for the "3". ***1/2Undertaker vs. JBL-WWE ChampionshipKinda boring, but an ok match. Orlando's constant interference and JBL's stiffness docked this match a couple points. Crowd must have all gone to the concession stand or restrooms or something, 'cause the audience is dead. 'Taker gets DQ'ed then puts JBL through the limo roof in a very fake but very cool chokeslam throught the "roof" ***, * for post match chokeslam.Randy Orton vs. Chris Benoit-World Heavyweight ChampionshipMatch of the night. Great wrestling performances I was an Orton follower and wanted to see him win without the help of Evolution, or weapons, or tight-grabbing, or rope-clenching, and I got to see what I wanted. I'm gonna go out on a limb and make this statement and I hope you guys don't get too offended: Orton "carried" Benoit to a great match. Excellent, an instant classic. *****P.S. Attention Neil Springer: Randy Orton is main event material and he carried Benoit to a great match.

reviewText: Rey Mysterio, Paul London, & Billy Kidman Vs. Dudley Boyz & Spike Dudley - This is a very exciting opening contest. Lots of action and exciting spots in this very fast paced opening match. This was a very good six man tag that never got boring. 3.5/5Kane Vs. Matt Hardy - This too, is a surprisingly good match even though the stpulation was that whoever wins the match they would have to "marry" Lita. Matt was taking bumps left and right while doing everything he could to stop the "Monstrious" Kane but in the end, Kane just overpowered Matt Hardy and chokeslammed Matt from the top rope for the win. Still, not a bad contest. 3.5/5John Cena Vs. United States Champion Booker T - This was match No. 1 in their Best Of 5 Series for Booker T's U.S. Title. Though not the greatest match, Booker T carried John Cena into a good match. A little bit short but still good. In the end, John Cena took the lead in the series after defeating Booker T with the F-U. 3.5/5Intercontinental ChampionshipEdge Vs. Chris Jericho Vs. Batista - This match here was the beginnings of Edge turning heel as he was booed in his hometown of Toronto while Batista was getting his push as he challenged for his first singles championship. Edge and Jericho gave a good performance while Batista delivered his powerhouse offense. Not the greatest but still a good Triple Threat Match. 3.75/5Kurt Angle Vs. Eddie Guerrero - This was Kurt Angle's first in-ring match since his neck injury earlier in the year as he battled the late, great Eddie Guerrero in a WrestleMania XX rematch but felt this match was a stepdown this from their previous encounter. Luther Reigns was in Kurt Angle's corner this time but had very little interaction in the match. This was a very good ground, mat-based match as Angle looked to be in great shape and looked very sharp in the ring ans at times seemed to be out-wrestling Eddie throughout the majority of the match. Still, another good encounter from these two and if you take special notice to the match, you will see that Kurt Angle and Eddie Guerrero does not take the match to the outside. 4/5Triple H Vs. Eugene - Euegene's overpush came to an end here as he wrestled his best match in his short, mediocre career where HHH carried Eugene to a seemingly okay match. But the big story here was the Toronto crowd booed Eugene and cheered for HHH who was in heel mode at full blast. Even displaying his heel mode as he fained a knee injury and tricked Eugene right before delivering a cheap shot to Eugene where the crowd loved it. The weakest match on the card but that isn't a bad thing as the match is watchable. 3/5Diva Dodgeball - This was pointless and had no reason to it. Take a look once and skip over it from there.WWE ChampionshipUndertaker Vs. J.B.L. - Though not a bad WWE Title Match, the fans however paid no attention to this match whatsoever. Their Last Ride Match heavily makes up for this okay WWE Title Match. In the end, the Undertaker beats JBL into a bloody heap while getting himself disqualified and chokeslamming JBL through the roof of his limo. 3.5/5World Heavyweight ChampionshipChris Benoit Vs. Randy Orton - These two went out there and delivered a wrestling clinic. Randy Orton lived up to his potential by having the best match of his career at this point while Chris Benoit went out and delivered a great performance as well. Possibably, the greatest main event in SummerSlam history. 5/5I recommend SummerSlam 2004. I felt it surpassed certain events in 2004 such as The Great American Bash, Judgment Day, & WrestleMania XX. Not the best SummerSlam but certainly not the worst.

reviewText: Hello and welcome to my review on Summerslam 2004. I use a grading system and each match receives a grade. Then to determine how the show ranks the total of the matches scores are divided by the number of matches giving the grade and a comment about whether you should buy it or not. The grading system is as follows.Grading E- =0-6.66%E =6.66-13.32%E+ =13.32-19.98%D- =19.98-26.64%D =26.64-33.30%D+ =33.30-39.96%C- =39.96-46.62%C =46.62-53.28%C+ =53.28-59.94%B- =59.94-66.60%B =66.60-73.26%B+ =73.26-79.92%A- =79.92-86.58%A =86.58-93.24%A+ = 93.24-100%Match One-Spike,D-Von And Bubba-Ray Dudley Vs Billy Kidman,Paul London And Rey Mysterio-Kidman and London had been feuding for a while and Spike had just turned on Mysterio and reunited with his brothers in the last few weeks. This match was fairly good with a hot tag, Spike feeling helpless and lots of high flying action. The ending was good as it told the story of what these teams are about. I would definetly rathered two title matches though. My rating 7.42/10.Match Two-Til Death Do Us Part Match-Kane Vs Matt Hardy-The winner of this match gets to marry Lita. Lita found out she is carrying Kanes kid as she'd slept with Kane to protect Matt. Matt then beat Kane in a no DQ match at Vengeance and now he's battling to win again. This match was fairly good considering the condition Hardy was in. Lots of spots and a few bumps and a good ending which made the nail in the coffin. My rating 7.15/10.Match Three-First Of Five Matches For The US Championship-Booker T(C)Vs John Cena-Kurt had stripped Cena of the title a while back and Cena was determined to get it back and when Kurt got put back on the active roster and Teddy Long became GM of Smackdown Cena got his chance to get it back in the best of five series. This match was way to short and it didn't tell the story it should have told. A bit of offence by both men then a quick ending which put a dampener on this already sloppy match. My rating 6.53/10.Match Four-Triple Threat-Intercontinental Championship-Edge(C)Vs Y2J Vs Batista-This was a average triple threat match with everyone dominating at different parts of the match. They were never all in the ring and it didn't feel like a good match. These wrestlers have a little chemistry together but Batista is still fairly green in the ring. The length was alright in my opinion but the ending was absolutely terrible. My rating 5.84/10.Match Five-Eddie Guerrero Vs Kurt Angle-Ever since the Smackdown Rumble back in January, Kurt has been trying to get rid of everything Eddie has worked to get like the WWE Title, he finally got it off Eddie after four months. Kurt had been Gm and Vince McMahon put Angle back on the active roster and made Eddie his opponent at Summerslam. This match was ordinary and nowhere near the standard of their Wrestlemania XX matchup. There was lots of finisher attempts, lying,cheating and stealing, submission moves and mocking each others moves. I liked it all except it was too short to be trying to mock each others moves and still get a good match. My rating 6.92/10.Match Six-HHH Vs Eugene-HHH invited Eugene to be a member of Evolution just after Bad Blood. Eugene accepted and HHH was playing Eugene using him to get what he wants the World Heavyweight Title. HHH finally got another shot at Benoit at Vengeance it looked like HHH was going to win as there was a ref bump and Hunter had the chair. Then Benoit and Eugene played tug of war with it til Benoit let go and Eugene smacked HHH in the face with the steel chair then Benoit rolled HHH up for the 1,2,3. A couple of weeks after on an episode of Raw HHH and Benoit had an ironman match for the Title. This time again HHH was dominating leading 3-1 with not long to go. Then Benoit fought back and evened it up at 3-3 and there was another ref bump and Eugene took out evolution and HHH and Benoit rolled over onto Hunter and pinned him 1,2,3. This set up there match at Summerslam. It was a good match with both men working great together. It had everything needed and it told a story very well. My rating 7.59/10.Match Seven-Diva Dodgeball-Team Diva Vs Team Dream-This wasn't an official match but it took up heaps of time and it was an absolute waste of time. My rating 0/10.Match Eight-WWE Championship-JBL(C)Vs Undertaker-This was an average match except it was way to long and the ending was very aggrivating. The work done by these two men was very satisfying and it showed that they both work hard. Hopefully this feud continues and gets a couple of rematches with gimmicks. My rating 7.01/10.Match Nine-Main Event-World Heavyweight Championship-Chris Benoit(C)Vs Randy Orton-Can Randy become the youngest champ ever or will Benoit out wrestle Orton and retain his strap? This was a good match and a very good choice for Main Event. The ending came out of absolutely nowhere. This was a clean match with no Evolution or anyone. My rating 7.97/10.This was a ordinary PPV. The scores for it was 56.43/90 which is an alright score. If we put that in a percentage it becomes 62.70% which is a little bit above average. The grade from the percentage is a B- which is alright but it should have been better for one of the big four PPVs of the year. The main highlights of this show are the World and WWE Title matches as well as Eddie Vs Kurt and Eugene Vs HHH. I would reccomend buying this as it is a fairly good show with lots of good action.

reviewText: Summerslam 2004 is my fourth summerslam and it is the second best out of all four. Each match was good, and though some of them could have been a lot better, the others more than make up for it. What came as a surprise was that all the people that my friends and I expected to win didn't. But after we got over our frustration and dissapointment, we realized this was an awsome PPV.The Dudley Boyz vs. Billy Kidman, Paul London, and Rey Mysterio: This was a good opener. I will agree with others and say it should have been a table elimination match, but other than that dissapointment, this was a solid opener. I like the Dudleys no matter what but they didn't have to cheat to win. 7.5/10Kane vs. Matt Hardy: This was an okay match, I think if it had a special stipulation to it it would have been better. Matt tried to be the aggresser and take control but Kane gave an unbelievable chokeslam off the top turnbuckle and got the win. The wedding by the way was totally surprising, and Kane would also chokeslam Matt of the stage through two tables! 7/10John Cena vs. Booker T: Oh boy, now how many times have I seen Cena against Booker? Hmmmm, to many times to remember. Anyway, the match was okay, but it was only the first one so it did not have my full attention. 7/10IC title match: What a surprise this was! I was into this match from start to finish which is a surprise to me because I am not the biggest fan of Batista. Edge gets booed out of his hometown and if you look closely you can see it was getting to him. I think it will be Edge vs. Jericho at Unforgiven. 8.5/10Diva Dodgeball: Oh my god, this did a pretty good job of wasting my life. Not much fun and "Team Dream" is kinda too into it, looked really fake for them. Christy is hot though. 5/10Kurt Angle vs. Eddie Guerrero: Another great technical battle between these two. Not as good as their match at WM but still good. Eddie tried to do the same thing he did at WM when he untied his shoe, but Kurt did the ankle lock on his bare foot and eddie tapped out. Still a good fight. 9/10JBL vs. Undertaker: The crowd was so bored in this one it was like watching something on TNA. Orlando Jordan throws the belt into the ring and the Undertaker gets DQ when he hit JBL on the head with it. A truly Holy Sh*t moment after the match when JBL got chokeslammed through his limo. Not through the sunroof, but the actuall metal. That moment saved it a little. 7/10HHH vs. Eugene: It was so annoying hearing everyone say Eugene would get his a** kicked by Triple H, and I'm glad that halfway through that match they finally shut up. HHH's performance is kinda far fetched, he kicks out of 3 or 4 finishing maneuvers from Eugene. And unfortunately not even Regal could save Eugene. However he does manage to knock Flair out, thank god. An okay match, but the wrong person won. 8/10Chris Benoit vs. Randy Orton: I admit it, I was hoping Benoit would win. But after seeing Randy as champ, I also have to admit that I am not as disapointed as I thought I would be. The crowd exploded after the match when Randy pinned Benoit. The match these two had the night after was good too, but this one was a historic moment. Randy became the real Next Big Thing, and I'm glad he is no longer part of Evolution. The end was good too, when both men shook hands in the ring. A great ending. 10/10Summerslam was awsome, no special matches yet this managed to keep me interested and entertained all the way through. I am glad this summerslam was actually good, rather than last years.

reviewText: The Event Was One Of The Most Historic And Greatest Ones In WWE, However I Can't Believe The WWE Production Crew Did Not Add Audio To The Last 13 Minutes, You Heard Beniot's Voice From That 13 Minutes In Raw Or The Next PPV ( I Forget), So They Must Have Had The Audio Backed Up Somewhere...  By Far The Greatest 13 Minutes Of The Event, And The Lack Of Audio There Dampened The Whole Event.  Just Another Example Of A Company Growing Mad With Power, And It Shows How WWE Has Become Aroggant Since The Days Of The Attitude ERA And The Alliance Vs WWE Days.  I Would Definately Not Be Dissappointed If Another Comapany Put The WWE Out Of Business, It Would Increase The Value Of My WWE DVDs Anyway.August 15, 2004Attendance Approx. 17,640Tronto, Canada- The Dudleys Boys VS Rey Mysterio, Billy Kidman, & Paul London- Kane VS Matt Hardy- John Cena VS Booker T (Match 1 Of Best Of 5 Series)- Edge (Champion) VS Batista VS Chris Jericho (For Intercontinental Championship )- Eddie Guerrero VS Kurt Angle w/ Luther Reigns- Triple H VS Eugene- Diva Dodgeball- Undertaker VS JBL (Champion) (For WWE Championship)- Chris Benoit (Champion) VS Randy Orton  (For World Heavyweight  Championship) NO AUDIO FOR LAST 13 MINUTES !!!EXTRAS- All the promos for summerslams themeFrom sunday night heat- Jericho interview- The Dudley's talking strategy- Rob Van Dam VS Rene dupreeDVD Exclusives- Evolutions reaction to Randy ortons Match- Eddie Guerrero confronts Chris Benoit- Team Dream From Diva Dodgeball Interview

reviewText: 40-50 Horrible PPV50-69 Bad PPV69-78 Decent PPV78-85 Good PPV85-92 Great PPV92+ EXCELLENT PPVSpike,Bubba,and D-von Dudley vs Billy Kidman,Paul London,and Rey-Good opener. The Dudleys are a great tag team to open with. Smackdown should have more of these six man tag matches. Nice spot when London flips onto Bubba. Dudleys hit the 3-D to win. Match Rating 7.5Till Death do us part match Kane vs Matt Hardy (Winner marries Lita)- Good Match. Even better than there Vengeance match and that was No DQ. Matt was good in this match. You think Matt is going to win with the bell then Kane kicks out. Kane wins with a chokeslam of the top rope. Match Rating 7Booker T vs John Cena 1st match out of 5 for US Title- This match was way to short. Booker dominates most of this one. This match was only like 7-9 minutes long. The F-U comes out of nowhere. Cena wins. Match Rating 6Triple Threat for the IC title Chris Jericho vs Batista vs Edge- Good Match. Most Triple Threat matches are good. Jericho is the best in this match. I think Batista should have won because he is the WHC currently and thats the only singles title he has won. Edge retains. Match Rating 6.5Kurt Angle vs Eddie Gurrureo- Great match. These two can meet and it is still always good. Eddie steals the Angle Slam and the Angle Lock. Angle unties Eddie's boot so he can't do what he did at WMXX. Angle wins via Submission. Match Rating 9Triple H vs Eugene- Triple H is great in this match. He first use Lilian to get Eugene distracted, then he fakes an injury to nail Eugene again. Eugene pulls some nice moves off like the Rock Bottom, Stunner, and the Hulkster Leg drop. Triple wins. Match Rating 8Diva Dodgeball Team Diva vs Team Dream- Stupid waste of time. Team Dream won. Not Even a match so no Rating.Undertaker vs JBL WWE Championship- I thought this match was actully really good. JBL performance was really good I thought. Orlando ruins the match by interfering when the ref is down. Then Taker hits JBL with the title and the ref sees it and he is DQed. JBL wins. Match Rating 8Randy Orton vs Chris Benoit World Heavyweight Championship- Great Match for Orton and Benoit. Orton should have stayed champion longer than a month. The Suicide Dive by Benoit looked like it hurt. RKO comes from nowhere. Orton wins. Match Rating 9Summerslam 2004 gets an 90 which means its a great ppv. HIGHLY RECOMMENDED. (Especially for Orton's victory over Benoit.)
